qas.question: What affects the climate in Europe?

answers.text: The altitude and size of the range

qas.question: What type of animal lives inn the higher peaks?
What plant grows in the rocky areas of the range?
Evidence of human habitation in the Alps goes as far back to what era?

context: <a0_0>The altitude and size of the range<a0_0/> affects the climate in Europe; in the mountains precipitation levels vary greatly and climatic conditions consist of distinct zones. Wildlife such as <a1_0>ibex<a1_0/> live in the higher peaks to elevations of 3,400 m (11,155 ft), and plants such as <a2_0>Edelweiss<a2_0/> grow in rocky areas in lower elevations as well as in higher elevations. Evidence of human habitation in the Alps goes back to the <a3_0>Paleolithic era<a3_0/>.
